◆ average_char_vector()

char average_char_vector ( Char *  vec)

This function will return the average value of the data in a vector data structure of type Short

/param vec A vector data structure of type Char /return avg The average value in the input data structure of type Char

Char vec;
init_char_vector(&vec, 5);
char a[5] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
insert_char_vector(&vec, a, 5, 0);
char b = average_char_vector(&vec);
PRINT(b);
// >> 3.00000
free_char_vector(&vec);

char *  value,
size_t  index 
)

This function will push a single string to an existing string vector container

/param vec A vector struct of type String /param value A string /param index The index where the string is to be pushed

#include "vector.h"
#include "print.h"
String vec;
init_string_vector(vec);
push_string_vector(&vec, "Hello", 0);
push_string_vector(&vec, "Goodbye", 1);
push_string_vector(&vec, "Again", 0);
PRINT(vec);
// >> [ Again, Hello, Goodbye ]
free_string_vector(&vec);

)

This function will add a range of data points to a vector data structure that start at a user defined data point and ends at another, or the nearest data point.

range_char_vector(&vec, 2, 20, 2);
PRINT(vec);

◆ replace_bool_vector_index()

3256 float number = interm;
3257 float start = 0.0f, end = number;
3258 float mid;
3259
3260 // To store the answer
3261 float ans = 0.;
3262 // To find integral part of square
3263 // root of number
3264 while (start <= end) {
3265 // Find mid
3266 mid = (start + end) / 2;
3267 // If number is perfect square
3268 // then break
3269 if (mid * mid == number) {
3270 ans = mid;
3271 break;
3272 }
3273 // Increment start if integral
3274 // part lies on right side
3275 // of the mid
3276 if (mid * mid < number) {
3277 //first start value should be added to answer
3278 ans=start;
3279 //then start should be changed
3280 start = mid + 1.f;
3281 }
3282 // Decrement end if integral part
3283 // lies on the left side of the mid
3284 else {
3285 end = mid - 1.f;
3286 }
3287 }
3288 // To find the fractional part
3289 // of square root upto 5 decimal
3290 float increment = 0.1f;
3291 for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
3292 while (ans * ans <= number) {
3293 ans += increment;
3294 }
3295 // Loop terminates,
3296 // when ans * ans > number
3297 ans = ans - increment;
3298 increment = increment / 10;
3299 }
3300 return ans;
3301}

3811 // of square root upto 5 decimal
3812 long double increment = 0.1;
3813 for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
3814 while (ans * ans <= number) {
3815 ans += increment;
3816 }
3817 // Loop terminates,
3818 // when ans * ans > number
3819 ans = ans - increment;
3820 increment = increment / 10;
3821 }
3822 return ans;
3823}
